  1448 				;###################################################################################################################
  1449 				; table of addresses for control sequences
  1450 				; entry format is this: final byte, intermediate byte, low address, high address
  1451 				; last entry has 0 for final byte
  1452 				; if there is no intermediate byte, then it is 0 in the entry.
  1453 				; I can either implement a sorted list here and do a binary search in the future, or I can implement a list sorted so that more common
  1454 				; control sequences come first. I don't know which I'll choose for the final design yet, but I'll choose at some point.
  1455
  1456 2E7A			ctrl_seq_table
  1457 2E7A 6D 00				.byte	'm', 0 
  1458 2E7C C0 2B				.word	SGR_adr			; set graphics rendition
  1459 2E7E 00					.byte	0			; this shows the end of the list.
  1460 						
